    'name' => 'image_comparator',
    'description' => 'Compare two images pixel-by-pixel using GD and generate a visual diff. Computes: number of different pixels, percentage difference, Mean Squared Error (MSE), Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR), and generates a diff image highlighting changes in red. Supports JPEG, PNG, GIF, WEBP, BMP inputs. Handles different-sized images (diff only overlapping area). First image comparison/diff capability in the ecosystem. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data.',
    'parameters' => 
